<h2>If you have Crohn's, you may be short on vitamin B-12.</h2>
</div>
<div class="slide_text">
<input id="q5" name="q5" type="hidden" value=""/>
<ul class="radio_inputs">
<li>
<a data-selected-answer="a" href="#">
<div class="answer_input_text">
<div class="input">a</div>
<p>True</p>
</div> </a>
</li>
<li>
<a data-selected-answer="b" href="#">
<div class="answer_input_text">
<div class="input">b</div>
<p>False</p>
</div> </a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="slide answer" data-slide-type="answer">
<div class="slide_content">
<div class="slide_media"> <div class="rmq_progress"><span class="cur_prog_title">Answer </span><span class="cur_prog_num">1</span>/<span class="tot_prog_num">13</span></div><div class="slide_question"><h2>If you have Crohn's, you may be short on vitamin B-12.</h2></div></div>
<div class="slide_text">
<ul class="rmq_answers">
<li class="user_answer">
<span class="answered_title"> </span>
<span class="you_answered_text">You answered: </span>
<span class="answer_text"> </span>
</li>
<li class="correct_answer">
<span class="answer_text_title">Correct Answer: </span>
<span class="answer_text"> </span>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="answer_expl">
<div class="expl_content">
<p>Crohn's can make it harder for your body to absorb certain vitamins and minerals, depending on where your disease is located. If it affects the lower end of your small intestine, your body may not take in enough B12 from your diet.</p>
<p>Crohn's can also make it hard for you to get enough folic acid, iron, and vitamins C and D. Ask your doctor if you need vitamins or other supplements.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
