<div class="slide_question">
<h2>Too much stress can bring on Crohn's disease.</h2>
</div>
<div class="slide_text">
<input id="q9" name="q9" type="hidden" value=""/>
<ul class="radio_inputs">
<li>
<a data-selected-answer="a" href="#">
<div class="answer_input_text">
<div class="input">a</div>
<p>True</p>
</div> </a>
</li>
<li>
<a data-selected-answer="b" href="#">
<div class="answer_input_text">
<div class="input">b</div>
<p>False</p>
</div> </a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="slide answer" data-slide-type="answer">
<div class="slide_content">
<div class="slide_media"> <div class="rmq_progress"><span class="cur_prog_title">Answer </span><span class="cur_prog_num">1</span>/<span class="tot_prog_num">13</span></div><div class="slide_question"><h2>Too much stress can bring on Crohn's disease.</h2></div></div>
<div class="slide_text">
<ul class="rmq_answers">
<li class="user_answer">
<span class="answered_title"> </span>
<span class="you_answered_text">You answered: </span>
<span class="answer_text"> </span>
</li>
<li class="correct_answer">
<span class="answer_text_title">Correct Answer: </span>
<span class="answer_text"> </span>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="answer_expl">
<div class="expl_content">
<p>Stress doesn't cause the disease. But it can make your symptoms worse. Living with this disease can also be stressful. You can take steps to keep it in line. Make it a habit to relax. Try deep breathing, yoga, tai chi, and meditation. Spend time with people you love and do things you enjoy. A support group and a counselor can help you handle your day-to-day life.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
